rComments: He is definitely terrible at explaining, but he will always take time outside of class to help the ones who ask for it.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read', 'Participation matters']

rComments: Friendly teacher Work hard to pass
The class itself is okay. Nice prof. It's easy to get good grades only if you memorize everything.
Awful class...I have to work harder than my other classes without any result, plus you have to learn by hard every detail of your lessons. If you can choose Aubert, do it
GOAT
Ce prof est dynamique et très intéressant!

Prof gentil mais cours quelque peu ennuyants. Si vous avez un cours de 3h avec lui, attendez vous qu'il prenne max 2h15. Il est un peu drôle. Étudiez bien pour ses tests par contre, il y a beaucoup de par coeur.

Very nice professor, had him in first year and once again on my last year. Caring and wants his students to succeed. Boring lectures but gives great real-life examples in class to make it easier to understand. No need to go to class but study all his revision questions!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class', 'Group projects']

rComments: Very very VERY boring. His accent makes me want to fall asleep. The course is ridiculously easy and straight from the textbook - do yourself a favour and get the same edition in English if you're an immersion student. Lectures were useless though as he explained everything poorly and slowly.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Very very difficult to follow as an immersion student because he goes so slow and has a difficult french accent. The material is present in a very boring way and he makes no effort to keep students engaged. Marking was fair, classes were bad. Best to learn out of the textbook.

I had a class with him where we had to do assignments every class. I would find so many mistakes in the correction and when I would tell him, he would take my assignments to adjust my grades. I never got my assignments back nor the adjusted grades. Emailed him and no response. He's not a horrible prof but I would take someone else instead if I can

Loved this professor. In-class lectures were fabulous and hilarious. Always told stories. Attendance is mandatory for DGDs. Exams are purely memorisation. With multiple, short answers, and long question (memorisation necessary). All the info is in the slides. Very genuine man. Never bought the textbook.

Seli is a great guy, he makes the boring lectures funny. He gives out extra marks for those who answer correctly his questions in class (0.00135%). questions on the chapter review are most likely to be on exam. the course only has one midterm and one final valued at 50% each. don't slack off.

Very very very easy class. The exams reflect all the subject covered in class and Seli was always available to answer our questions after class and during office hours. He is funny and takes the time to really teach the subjects. I would take again!

The professor is a genuine guy but his grading criteria is awful. He is very unforgiving when it comes to marking and there is absolutely no clear grading criteria. You can do very well one assignment and fail the next. The content is not difficult, but the sheer incompetence of the grading criteria AND TA's makes this class all luck.

He is very nice and open to answering questions. If you visit him during his office hours, he'll tell you specifically what he requires in the devoir. The actual lecture is pretty useless though. Everything you need is on the slides that he sends.

There is one midterm, final exam, two "devoir", and weekly DGD. For a 7-10pm class, he is very boring as he takes forever to finish one slide to repeat everything it is saying in different words. Honestly a useless class that lacks substance, but that is hardly the prof's fault. Just memorize the information and you'll get an A.

Honestly this teacher is the best. he tries his best to help his students and genuinely   cares unlike other teachers. I would take him again any day.  if you have any questions or any concerns just go see him and he will do his best to help you!  - You need to study his midterms/exams are a bit hard
He's a kind prof, but you're going to have to memorize A LOT of powerpoint slides. Exams are long and boring, but are very well reflected in the practice questions.
Hard exam but if you study your good.

He is a really nice person but as a teacher it's different. The only thing he does is reading is powerpoints so going to class is actually pretty useless. Exams are much  more about your ability to memorize definitions than actual knowledge of the matter. Sometimes I wonder if he has actual experience in what he is teaching.

This teacher wont give quiz and lot of exams there is only two exams midterm and final. If you go see him he is very helpfull and nice. I used to always skip his class and still had a good grade he also gives 0.075 points or 1 point for participation... Wich is whatever since it's so little but he is a good teacher
pretty good teacher but the exams are quite hard unless your name is Michael Ross and can remember evertything that appears on his slides.
